    "type": "Question",
    "name": "Question 4 @ 2022/2023",
    "Question": {
      "content": "The material between the plates of a capacitor is",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "Polarization",
        "Dielectric",
        "Charge",
        "ionic"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "Dielectric"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "<div style='font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.6;'><h3 style='color: #2c3e50;'>Role of Dielectrics in Capacitors</h3><p>A dielectric is an insulating material placed between capacitor plates to:</p><ul><li><strong>Increase capacitance</strong> by reducing the effective electric field.</li><li><strong>Prevent arcing</strong> between plates.</li></ul><h4 style='color: #2c3e50; margin-top: 15px;'>Why Other Options Are Incorrect:</h4><ul><li><strong>Polarization</strong>: A process where dielectric atoms align, not a material.</li><li><strong>Charge</strong>: Refers to stored electrons, not the material.</li><li><strong>Ionic</strong>: Describes bonding, not a capacitor component.</li></ul><p>Thus, <strong>Dielectric</strong> is the correct term.</p></div>"
    },
    "topic": [
      "Capacitance",
      "Electrostatics",
      "Dielectrics"
    ]
