  {
    "type": "Question",
    "name": "Question 22 @ 2022/2023",
    "Question": {
      "content": "The plates of a 4.0F capacitor is separated by 2.5mm air gap. Calculate the area of the plates.",
      "type": "subJective"
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "1.13×10⁹ m²"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "<div style='font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.6;'><h3 style='color: #2c3e50;'>Parallel Plate Capacitor Area</h3><p>Using the capacitance formula:</p><p style='background: #f8f9fa; padding: 10px; border-left: 4px solid #3498db;'><strong>C = ε₀A/d ⇒ A = Cd/ε₀</strong></p><h4 style='color: #2c3e50; margin-top: 15px;'>Calculation:</h4><p>A = (4.0F × 2.5×10⁻³m) / (8.85×10⁻¹²F/m) ≈ <strong>1.13×10⁹ m²</strong></p><p style='color: #e74c3c;'><em>Note: This unrealistically large area suggests the capacitance value may be incorrect (likely should be µF).</em></p></div>"
    },
    "topic": [
      "Capacitance",
